{[#]How would you start your counterplay with Black, by pawn breaks or piece
pressure?} 12... Nb6 {This is the best plan.} ({In this case the typical} 12...
e5 $2 {runs into} 13. b4 Qc7 14. Bh2 $16 {leaving Black under a nasty pin.})
13. b4 (13. Bb3 Nfd5 {attacks f4 and c3, more or less forcing} 14. Nxd5 cxd5 {
with just symbolic white advantage.}) 13... Qf5 14. g4 {Enabling Bd3.} Qd7 15.
Bd3 Nbd5 16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Rb3 (17. Bg3 {allows} e5 {since} 18. dxe5 Nc3 {
wins an exchange.}) 17... Nxf4 18. Qxf4 Rac8 19. b5 e5 (19... c5 $1 {may even
be slightly better for Black.}) 20. dxe5 {1/2 Najdorf-Milic, Bled 1950.}
1/2-1/2

