Bxf3 15. Bxf3 dxc4 16. Rxc4 e5 17. Bg3 exd4 18. exd4 {/\Rb4} a5 19. d5 $36) 15.
cxd5 {Once again it is difficult avoiding commitments.} (15. Rc3 dxc4 16. Bxc4
(16. Rxc4 Bd5 17. Ra4 Rfd8 {[%cal Gc6c5]}) 16... Rad8 17. Rb3 Qa7 {We can see
that the a7-square can also be useful.}) (15. a3 dxc4 16. Bxc4 Bxf3 17. gxf3 e5
18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Bxe5 Bxe5 20. Qc2 Kg7 21. Rd7 Qxb2 {and the a3-pawn is
hanging.}) (15. h3 $5 dxc4 16. Bxc4 Bxf3 17. gxf3 Qb4 18. Qc2 e6 19. a3 Qe7 $11
) 15... Bxd5 16. e4 {Jussupow's recommendation.} Bxe4 17. Bxh6 Bd5 $5 {This
looks safest.} (17... a4 18. Rc3 Qa5 19. h4 (19. Qc1 $5 Bd5 20. Nh4 {[%cal
Gc3h3] followed by the rook transfer to the kingside may be dangerous.}) 19...
a3 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. bxa3 Rh8 22. Qb2 Nf6 {Laznicka,V (2610)-Navara,D (2656)
Czechia 2007 (½-½, 37)}) 18. h4 Qb4 19. Rc3 Nf6 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. a3 Qd6 22.
Ng5 Rh8 $11 *

