{Do you remember what is Black's best plan after 7.h3?} 7... Ne4 $1 {This is
the best move in the position. Black should create threats before White
manages to comfortably develop his pieces. The main line goes:} 8. Bd3 Qa5 $1 {
Another precise move. The pin along the a5-e1 diagonal is very characteristic
for this variation.} 9. cxd5 Nxc3 10. Qd2 cxd5 {With a nice position for Black.
Later on, he will put pressure on the backward pawn on c3.} *

