{[#]} {Are you going to take the h4-bishop?} 13... Bc8 $1 {It would be a
mistake to take the bishop on h4, because then the bishop on h4, because then
White wins the knight on h5 with a better game. On the other hand, White's
threat was 14.Bxg5 fxg5 15.Nxg5 simultaneously attacking the knight and the
bishop.} 14. O-O {How can Black create counterplay here?} e5 $1 {This thematic
break is the right approach to the position.} 15. dxe5 gxh4 16. Nxh4 fxe5 {
In a long-term, the bishop pair and the strong center will compensate the
missing pawn.} *

