{How Black should arrange his pieces here?} 11... Qb6 $1 {This is better than
11...e5} 12. Rfd1 Rfd8 13. Nc4 Qa6 {This is the best square for the queen in
such structures. From a6, the queen avoids the opposition with White's rooks
and exerces pressure on the queenside.} 14. Bf1 {Now, it is time to bring our
last passive piece into play.} Rac8 15. a4 Na5 {Black's pieces are very well
placed and White should be carefull to maintain the ballance.} *

